messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Files containing the handler implementations:
- users/routers.go

Explanation:
- hello.go registers users.UserRegister at the route group v1.Group("/user"), so I searched the codebase for "UserRegister".
- The search shows the definition and the HTTP handler implementations are in users/routers.go. That file defines the UserRegister(router *gin.RouterGroup) function and the actual handlers UserRetrieve and UserUpdate that are registered for GET and PUT on "/".
- I ignored test files (e.g., users/unit_test.go) as requested; although a test references UserRegister, the real handler implementations live in users/routers.go.
